      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI directly linked to clinical failure modes; stiffness and yield force relevant to construct integrity under physiological loading.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with bone graft; yield force and F@40mm bound plastic deformation risk. QoI selection endorsed by clinical consultants as representative of failure risk in lumbar fusion applications."
    },
